column5: hey guys due to the low water level we cant launch our 17 foot fiberglass boat anywhere in bark lake or in the matawaska were pretty much pooched for fishing any of that strech so my question is where are some lakes that have decent launches in that area in a river or lake that has decent fishing for pike, walleye, or any trout thanks a ton we will be heading out for camp tonight hopefully we can figure something out before that
Barrysbay has a great public launch right in town behind the big church. It's on Kamaniskeg lake, and it's free imagine that.
The launch in the town of madawaska is too low?
